definition: to receive/to accept/to collect/to put away/to restrain/to stop/in care of (used on address line after name)
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: To obtain a gold or platinum card you will need to have a higher annual income.
sentences.chinese: 獲得金牌或白金卡，你必須有較高的年收入。

sentences.english: The amount you’re left with is your true take-home salary for your job for a year.
sentences.chinese: 你剩下的總數纔是你從工作中帶回家的真實年收入。

sentences.english: The average annual earnings of high school dropouts are significantly less than the average annual earnings of high school graduates.
sentences.chinese: 高中輟學者的平均年收入要顯著低於高中畢業生。

sentences.english: In America alone , tipping is a $16 billion-a-year industry .
sentences.chinese: 僅在美國，小費就是一個年收入160億美元的行業。

sentences.english: Please provide details of your estimated annual income & net worth, excluding your primary residence.
sentences.chinese: 請提供您的估計年收入的和除主住房外的淨資產值。

sentences.english: She estimates annual industry revenue at about T$5.8bn.
sentences.chinese: 她估計，該行業的全年收入總額大約爲58億新臺幣。

sentences.english: A wage rise of 5% represents an annual increase of 250 for the lowest-paid workers.
sentences.chinese: 對收入最低的工人來說相當於全年收入增加。

sentences.english: The uneven of area economy development is principal influencing factor.
sentences.chinese: 地區經濟發展的不平衡性是影響年收入的重要因素。

sentences.english: The median household income in Australia is A$67, 000.
sentences.chinese: 而澳大利亞的家庭平均年收入爲六萬七千澳元。

sentences.english: A thousand dollars is earmarked for research.
sentences.chinese: 年收入總共一萬五千美元。

sentences.english: Average income in America was $38, 615 in 2007.
sentences.chinese: 2007年美國的平均年收入是38615美元。
